1
00:00:11,767 --> 00:00:13,433
Madam, calm down.

2
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:14,633
Check our house

3
00:00:14,700 --> 00:00:16,633
because I can't reach
my daughter and her nanny.

4
00:00:16,700 --> 00:00:18,133
Looks like no one is here.

5
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:19,167
What?

6
00:00:19,233 --> 00:00:20,967
Are you sure you're allergic
to pistachios?

7
00:00:21,033 --> 00:00:23,300
Does it mean my mom made
the wrong diagnosis?

8
00:00:23,367 --> 00:00:24,267
Come on, let's play.
My treat.

9
00:00:25,033 --> 00:00:26,300
Zayn is here, too!

10
00:00:26,367 --> 00:00:27,600
Why is he with a weirdo?

11
00:00:27,667 --> 00:00:28,967
You know what to do.

12
00:00:29,033 --> 00:00:29,833
I'll be right back.
Stay here.

13
00:00:30,667 --> 00:00:31,767
- Hi!
- Hi!

14
00:00:31,833 --> 00:00:32,833
Stop!

15
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:35,300
Who told you Olive Caparas
was a doctor?

16
00:00:35,400 --> 00:00:37,133
Mookie might have
been kidnapped!

17
00:00:37,200 --> 00:00:40,000
You'll deal with me if something
terrible happens to her!

18
00:00:40,067 --> 00:00:41,233
Are you flirting with Zayn?

19
00:00:41,300 --> 00:00:42,133
Of course not!

20
00:00:42,200 --> 00:00:43,233
Zayn gave that to me!

21
00:00:43,300 --> 00:00:44,000
Stop!

22
00:00:44,067 --> 00:00:45,033
Ma'am Olive!

23
00:00:46,067 --> 00:00:46,900
That's Stacy and her friends.
Did Zayn give this to you, too?

24
00:00:47,933 --> 00:00:49,333
My mom gave it to me.

25
00:00:50,033 --> 00:00:51,100
Move!

26
00:00:51,167 --> 00:00:52,233
Mookie, are you okay?

27
00:00:52,300 --> 00:00:53,467
Give that to me!

28
00:00:53,533 --> 00:00:54,567
Give me that!

29
00:01:30,533 --> 00:01:31,000
No!

30
00:01:31,767 --> 00:01:35,633
Sorry, I didn't mean it.
I was worried about Mookie.

31
00:01:35,700 --> 00:01:37,400
Why are you ganging up on her?

32
00:01:37,467 --> 00:01:38,467
Shut up!

33
00:01:38,533 --> 00:01:40,033
I will tell my mom on you!

34
00:01:40,100 --> 00:01:42,433
We will file a child abuse case
against you!

35
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:43,967
I have witnesses.

36
00:01:44,033 --> 00:01:45,667
My friends!

37
00:01:45,733 --> 00:01:48,167
What if Mookie charges you
with kidnapping?

38
00:01:48,767 --> 00:01:50,733
We have CCTV evidence.

39
00:01:51,667 --> 00:01:55,233
And Mookie can also charge you
with a bullying case.

40
00:01:55,300 --> 00:01:56,733
She also has a witness.

41
00:01:56,800 --> 00:01:57,867
Me.

42
00:01:57,933 --> 00:02:01,667
Stop bullying Mookie
if you want us to stay friends.

43
00:02:01,733 --> 00:02:02,767
All of you, too.

44
00:02:06,967 --> 00:02:07,600
Go on.

45
00:02:08,133 --> 00:02:09,000
Leave.

46
00:02:09,600 --> 00:02:10,800
Don't do this again.

47
00:02:22,567 --> 00:02:24,567
I'm sorry for what they did,
Mookie.

48
00:02:27,233 --> 00:02:28,467
I want to stay with you.

49
00:02:28,533 --> 00:02:31,433
But I still have dinner
with my dad.

50
00:02:34,467 --> 00:02:35,267
It's okay.

51
00:02:36,400 --> 00:02:39,167
I'm sorry that I yelled at you
earlier.

52
00:02:39,233 --> 00:02:40,567
It's okay, Emma.

53
00:02:40,633 --> 00:02:41,733
It's my fault, anyway.

54
00:02:42,500 --> 00:02:43,167
Bye.

55
00:02:43,600 --> 00:02:44,733
Mookie, sorry.

56
00:02:46,933 --> 00:02:48,700
Mookie, dear.

57
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:49,933
Do you still want
to go around?

58
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,133
It's still early.

59
00:02:51,200 --> 00:02:53,100
Wait. Let me see
what time it is.

60
00:02:53,167 --> 00:02:53,967
Wait.

61
00:02:55,433 --> 00:02:56,800
5:30.

62
00:02:57,400 --> 00:02:59,533
Why is my mother calling me?

63
00:02:59,600 --> 00:03:01,133
Wait, I'll just call her.

64
00:03:06,967 --> 00:03:08,667
Emma, what's wrong with you?

65
00:03:08,733 --> 00:03:10,567
I've been calling you.

66
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:13,800
I'm sorry, my phone
is in silent mode.

67
00:03:13,867 --> 00:03:14,733
Why?

68
00:03:14,800 --> 00:03:16,567
Have you brought Mookie home?

69
00:03:16,633 --> 00:03:19,133
Ma'am Olive has been discharged
from the hospital!

70
00:03:19,200 --> 00:03:19,700
What?

71
00:04:00,033 --> 00:04:03,667
Mother, what do we do?

72
00:04:03,733 --> 00:04:05,700
I don't know, too, Mookie.

73
00:04:05,767 --> 00:04:06,767
I don't know.

74
00:04:07,233 --> 00:04:08,567
What do we do?

75
00:04:10,800 --> 00:04:12,067
Wait. I have an idea.

76
00:04:25,400 --> 00:04:26,333
Hey, Ems.
Why?

77
00:04:27,300 --> 00:04:29,100
Dan, I hope you're near
the mall.

78
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,867
Yes, I'm near the mall.

79
00:04:30,933 --> 00:04:32,000
I'm less than a kilometer away.

80
00:04:32,067 --> 00:04:33,267
Why? What's the matter?

81
00:04:33,333 --> 00:04:35,267
We need to go home.

82
00:04:35,333 --> 00:04:36,600
Ma'am Olive is on her way home.

83
00:04:36,667 --> 00:04:38,100
We need to be there
before she does.

84
00:04:38,600 --> 00:04:39,300
Okay, okay.

85
00:04:39,367 --> 00:04:40,367
I'll be there.

86
00:04:59,300 --> 00:05:00,167
Dammit!

87
00:05:02,300 --> 00:05:03,300
Emma?

88
00:05:03,367 --> 00:05:04,533
Mookie?

89
00:05:05,433 --> 00:05:07,233
I'm back!

90
00:05:07,300 --> 00:05:10,900
Emma, Mookie, I'm back!

91
00:05:10,967 --> 00:05:11,667
Emma!

92
00:05:12,433 --> 00:05:13,433
Mookie!

93
00:05:13,500 --> 00:05:14,233
Where are they?

94
00:05:15,267 --> 00:05:18,633
Emma, Mookie, I'm back!

95
00:05:24,000 --> 00:05:24,667
Where are they?

96
00:05:24,733 --> 00:05:25,733
Emma!

97
00:05:25,800 --> 00:05:26,500
Mookie!

98
00:05:27,267 --> 00:05:28,433
Where are they?

99
00:05:30,500 --> 00:05:31,333
Emma!

100
00:05:34,000 --> 00:05:36,900
Emma, the mall is nearer
to the house than the hospital.

101
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:39,367
I'm sure, we'll be there
before she does.

102
00:05:39,433 --> 00:05:40,967
Dan, she left the hospital
a while ago.

103
00:05:41,033 --> 00:05:42,900
I know a couple of shortcuts.

104
00:05:42,967 --> 00:05:45,033
I'm sure, we'll be there
before she does.

105
00:05:45,100 --> 00:05:45,867
Don't worry.

106
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:16,633
Come on, come on.

107
00:06:19,733 --> 00:06:21,367
Mookie.

108
00:06:21,433 --> 00:06:22,400
Let me.

109
00:06:33,033 --> 00:06:34,300
Looks like Ma'am Olive
isn't here yet.

110
00:06:34,367 --> 00:06:35,333
- Bring Mookie inside.
- Okay.

111
00:06:35,400 --> 00:06:36,300
I'll open the gate.

112
00:06:42,733 --> 00:06:43,200
Dan!
Hurry!

113
00:06:43,867 --> 00:06:45,300
It might be my mom.

114
00:06:45,733 --> 00:06:46,833
Hide.

115
00:06:46,900 --> 00:06:47,700
Go hide somewhere. Hurry!

116
00:06:52,333 --> 00:06:53,033
Yes.

117
00:06:53,100 --> 00:06:54,933
This address is wrong.

118
00:06:56,033 --> 00:06:57,467
Text me the address.

119
00:06:58,200 --> 00:06:59,867
I'm already far.

120
00:06:59,933 --> 00:07:01,000
Yes. Okay.

121
00:07:13,733 --> 00:07:15,633
Flor, why is the door open?

122
00:07:16,367 --> 00:07:17,533
Flor!

123
00:07:19,167 --> 00:07:20,033
Flor!

124
00:07:21,900 --> 00:07:22,433
Flor!

125
00:07:22,500 --> 00:07:23,467
Madam!

126
00:07:26,767 --> 00:07:27,700
- Flor!
- Madam!

127
00:07:28,433 --> 00:07:29,067
Flor!

128
00:07:29,133 --> 00:07:30,800
Madam!

129
00:07:30,867 --> 00:07:31,767
Hello!

130
00:07:32,667 --> 00:07:34,233
- Hello!
- What are you doing here?

131
00:07:35,200 --> 00:07:37,667
Are you following me
all the way home?

132
00:07:39,267 --> 00:07:41,467
Madam, you escaped from me.

133
00:07:41,533 --> 00:07:44,367
I was chasing your car.

134
00:07:44,900 --> 00:07:48,833
Are you going to forget
what you owe me?

135
00:07:48,933 --> 00:07:51,167
Payment for my services
and for the card games.

136
00:07:51,233 --> 00:07:51,933
You lost.

137
00:07:52,567 --> 00:07:53,967
You lost a lot.

138
00:07:54,033 --> 00:07:55,667
Are you not going to pay me?

139
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:58,033
You really are something.

140
00:07:58,100 --> 00:08:01,500
All this time, you've been
saying that you did all that

141
00:08:01,567 --> 00:08:03,267
because you wanted
to take care of me.

142
00:08:03,333 --> 00:08:04,367
That's true.

143
00:08:04,433 --> 00:08:06,867
But turns out you'll ask
for payment.

144
00:08:09,000 --> 00:08:10,133
- Madam.
- Stop!

145
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:11,033
Stop!

146
00:08:11,700 --> 00:08:12,467
I'm going to fall!

147
00:08:12,533 --> 00:08:13,600
What are you doing?

148
00:08:13,667 --> 00:08:14,967
Let go of me!

149
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:18,100
I'm just assisting you.

150
00:08:18,167 --> 00:08:19,533
You know?

151
00:08:19,600 --> 00:08:21,633
I was really planning
to give you money.

152
00:08:22,600 --> 00:08:24,700
I actually liked what you did.

153
00:08:24,767 --> 00:08:26,233
Because...

154
00:08:26,300 --> 00:08:28,267
you did all of that
because you said,

155
00:08:28,333 --> 00:08:29,567
you wanted to take care of me.

156
00:08:30,233 --> 00:08:32,667
- Yes.
- Even though you're only

157
00:08:32,733 --> 00:08:34,933
doing it for money.

158
00:08:35,000 --> 00:08:35,833
Of course not.

159
00:08:35,900 --> 00:08:37,133
I don't want to call
this payment.

160
00:08:37,200 --> 00:08:38,367
But a token of gratitude.

161
00:08:39,000 --> 00:08:42,000
But I really should call this
a payment.

162
00:08:42,067 --> 00:08:43,800
Because you're greedy for money!

163
00:08:46,267 --> 00:08:48,233
Madam, thank you.

164
00:08:48,667 --> 00:08:50,767
- What are you doing?
- You're so generous.

165
00:08:50,833 --> 00:08:52,233
Let go of me!

166
00:08:52,300 --> 00:08:53,000
What are you doing?
Madam, your hair smells good.

167
00:08:54,100 --> 00:08:55,900
It feels good to hug you.

168
00:08:57,467 --> 00:08:58,367
Madam!
Let go of me!

169
00:08:59,133 --> 00:09:00,767
I might not see you again.

170
00:09:00,833 --> 00:09:01,600
I will miss you.

171
00:09:01,667 --> 00:09:03,433
That's why I'm hugging you.

172
00:09:09,133 --> 00:09:10,433
Oh, Emma!

173
00:09:10,500 --> 00:09:12,133
I'm glad you're back.

174
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,733
I don't know what to tell
Ma'am Olive

175
00:09:13,800 --> 00:09:14,633
if she asks where you are.

176
00:09:14,700 --> 00:09:15,867
Where did you go?

177
00:09:15,933 --> 00:09:16,867
We went to the arcade.

178
00:09:16,933 --> 00:09:18,467
- Arcade?
- Save your lecture for later.

179
00:09:18,533 --> 00:09:19,200
Hurry!

180
00:09:19,267 --> 00:09:20,867
Help me get Mookie upstairs.

181
00:09:20,933 --> 00:09:22,467
Ma'am Olive will be here
any minute.

182
00:09:22,533 --> 00:09:23,233
Let's hurry.

183
00:09:23,300 --> 00:09:24,700
- Faster.
- The oxygen!

184
00:09:24,767 --> 00:09:25,667
- It's here.
- Oh, dear!
Check if Ma'am Olive
is already there!

185
00:09:27,300 --> 00:09:28,767
I said let go of me!

186
00:09:28,867 --> 00:09:29,900
Stop!

187
00:09:29,967 --> 00:09:30,733
There you go.

188
00:09:32,133 --> 00:09:34,667
Maybe, later, you'll charge me
for your flattery!

189
00:09:37,100 --> 00:09:38,733
You almost made me believe

190
00:09:38,800 --> 00:09:40,567
that everything you showed me
was true.

191
00:09:41,700 --> 00:09:44,567
You are nothing but a leech!

192
00:09:45,367 --> 00:09:47,300
You are a leech
that's greedy for money!

193
00:09:47,367 --> 00:09:49,267
There, there. Let's hurry.

194
00:09:49,333 --> 00:09:50,033
Let's get the wheelchair.

195
00:09:50,533 --> 00:09:51,967
Ma'am Olive might be here
any moment.

196
00:09:52,033 --> 00:09:52,967
Hold it at the back.
Wait.

197
00:09:54,500 --> 00:09:55,833
There, there.

198
00:10:01,300 --> 00:10:01,900
Flor!

199
00:10:03,100 --> 00:10:03,900
Flor!

200
00:10:13,033 --> 00:10:14,300
Madam!

201
00:10:14,533 --> 00:10:15,367
Let me assist you.

202
00:10:15,433 --> 00:10:16,567
It's not easy to take
the stairs.

203
00:10:16,633 --> 00:10:17,400
You might fall.
What do you want?

204
00:10:18,933 --> 00:10:19,967
You're going to fall...

205
00:10:20,033 --> 00:10:21,933
Won't you leave me alone?

206
00:10:23,133 --> 00:10:24,600
Don't get mad.

207
00:10:24,667 --> 00:10:27,933
I can give you back the money
if you like.

208
00:10:28,000 --> 00:10:29,733
I'm just joking.

209
00:10:29,800 --> 00:10:30,767
Joke, joke, joke.

210
00:10:30,833 --> 00:10:31,767
No, it's not!

211
00:10:32,700 --> 00:10:33,433
It was just a joke.

212
00:10:33,500 --> 00:10:35,033
You really are greedy for money.

213
00:10:36,833 --> 00:10:37,367
There!

214
00:10:38,667 --> 00:10:39,700
I gave you the money, right?

215
00:10:39,767 --> 00:10:40,833
What else do you need?

216
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:44,367
Get out of here before
I charge you with trespassing.

217
00:10:44,433 --> 00:10:45,200
Madam.
One.

218
00:10:46,500 --> 00:10:47,367
Please.
Two.

219
00:10:47,933 --> 00:10:49,167
Please don't.

220
00:10:49,233 --> 00:10:49,933
Three.

221
00:10:51,367 --> 00:10:52,800
Are you leaving or not?

222
00:10:57,767 --> 00:10:58,533
Flor!

223
00:10:59,267 --> 00:11:00,467
I'm leaving.

224
00:11:01,567 --> 00:11:02,500
Flor!

225
00:11:05,133 --> 00:11:07,500
Flor, make this woman leave.

226
00:11:25,200 --> 00:11:25,667
Hey.

227
00:11:26,367 --> 00:11:27,333
Get out of here.

228
00:11:27,400 --> 00:11:28,067
Go.

229
00:11:28,133 --> 00:11:29,133
I hear Ma'am Olive already.

230
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:29,800
Hurry up!

231
00:11:42,100 --> 00:11:42,867
Wait, Mother.

232
00:11:42,933 --> 00:11:44,567
My necklace.

233
00:11:44,633 --> 00:11:45,167
The necklace?
- Yes.
- Hurry up!

234
00:11:45,733 --> 00:11:46,967
We'll get caught!

235
00:11:47,033 --> 00:11:48,267
I can hear her already.

236
00:11:48,333 --> 00:11:48,900
What are you doing?

237
00:11:48,967 --> 00:11:50,333
Go hide already!

238
00:11:54,367 --> 00:11:55,767
There, there, there.

239
00:11:55,833 --> 00:11:57,333
Make sure she won't see you.

240
00:11:59,900 --> 00:12:00,467
Flor.
Yes, Ma'am.

241
00:12:01,267 --> 00:12:02,867
Don't you hear me?

242
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:04,400
I've been calling you.

243
00:12:05,533 --> 00:12:06,467
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

244
00:12:06,533 --> 00:12:07,767
I was busy.

245
00:12:07,833 --> 00:12:08,767
I didn't hear you.

246
00:12:09,567 --> 00:12:10,467
Fine!
Get out of the room.

247
00:12:11,333 --> 00:12:11,900
Yes, Ma'am.

248
00:12:11,967 --> 00:12:13,100
I'm sorry again, Ma'am.

249
00:12:18,500 --> 00:12:19,133
Mommy.

250
00:12:21,600 --> 00:12:23,633
So, you've been discharged
already.

251
00:12:23,700 --> 00:12:25,100
I thought it was tomorrow.

252
00:12:25,867 --> 00:12:28,700
Well, I had to sign a waiver
for them to release me.

253
00:12:29,333 --> 00:12:32,167
I needed to go home because
I couldn't reach Flor.

254
00:12:32,233 --> 00:12:34,400
I didn't know what was
happening in the house.

255
00:12:34,733 --> 00:12:36,200
I'm glad you're okay now.

256
00:12:37,067 --> 00:12:37,933
No, I'm not.

257
00:12:40,367 --> 00:12:41,500
Why are you smiling?

258
00:12:42,433 --> 00:12:44,767
Does it look funny to you
that I'm on crutches?

259
00:12:45,733 --> 00:12:47,700
No. Of course not, Mommy.

260
00:12:47,800 --> 00:12:51,167
I'm just relieved that
you're okay and back home.

261
00:12:51,800 --> 00:12:53,233
I am not okay.

262
00:13:00,100 --> 00:13:01,467
Where is your necklace?

263
00:13:03,367 --> 00:13:05,833
My necklace, Mommy.
It's just here on the...

264
00:13:08,500 --> 00:13:09,700
Let me get it.

265
00:13:09,767 --> 00:13:11,767
It's okay, Mommy.

266
00:13:11,833 --> 00:13:13,400
- Why?
- It's okay.

267
00:13:13,467 --> 00:13:16,433
Do you think I can't pick it up
because I'm on crutches?

268
00:13:17,400 --> 00:13:18,367
I can do it.

269
00:13:30,767 --> 00:13:31,467
Mother.

270
00:13:32,533 --> 00:13:33,367
What's going on inside?

271
00:13:33,433 --> 00:13:34,567
Did Olive catch them?

272
00:13:37,233 --> 00:13:37,633
Mother.

273
00:13:47,300 --> 00:13:48,600
There it is.

274
00:14:05,633 --> 00:14:07,867
Why is your necklace broken?

275
00:14:12,033 --> 00:14:15,433
I was combing my hair
earlier, Mommy.

276
00:14:15,500 --> 00:14:17,867
I think it got stuck
in my hairbrush.

277
00:14:21,833 --> 00:14:22,533
Okay.

278
00:14:23,767 --> 00:14:24,700
Get some rest.

279
00:14:25,833 --> 00:14:27,000
I'll be downstairs.

280
00:14:53,733 --> 00:14:55,033
Thank you, Mother.

281
00:14:59,933 --> 00:15:01,833
This is the only time
I've been happy

282
00:15:01,933 --> 00:15:03,867
since we lost Baby Kayla.

283
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:06,600
Thank you, too.

284
00:15:07,633 --> 00:15:09,500
I really had fun.

285
00:15:14,067 --> 00:15:15,433
I need to go.

286
00:15:16,467 --> 00:15:17,533
Okay.

287
00:15:20,867 --> 00:15:21,433
Bye.

288
00:15:42,667 --> 00:15:44,000
Where is it?

289
00:15:53,133 --> 00:15:54,467
Ems, what are you looking for?

290
00:15:55,467 --> 00:15:57,033
My coin purse.

291
00:15:57,100 --> 00:15:59,567
I was planning to buy you
and mother some soda.

292
00:16:00,433 --> 00:16:03,733
Maybe you dropped it at the mall

293
00:16:03,800 --> 00:16:05,233
because you and Mookie
were in a hurry.

294
00:16:07,233 --> 00:16:07,967
Maybe.

295
00:16:08,867 --> 00:16:09,900
What a waste of money.

296
00:16:10,433 --> 00:16:12,000
It's 180 pesos.

297
00:16:12,067 --> 00:16:13,067
Yeah, what a waste.

298
00:16:13,133 --> 00:16:16,200
But thanks to you and mother
for your help.

299
00:16:16,667 --> 00:16:18,567
You're welcome.

300
00:16:19,100 --> 00:16:23,600
But later, tell me what you did
at the mall.

301
00:16:23,667 --> 00:16:24,733
Tell me everything.

302
00:16:26,167 --> 00:16:26,933
Danilo.

303
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:29,300
- Mother.
- You seem to be interested

304
00:16:29,367 --> 00:16:30,633
in Madam Olive's daughter, too.

305
00:16:32,067 --> 00:16:34,967
I can't explain, Mother.
I also wonder.

306
00:16:36,000 --> 00:16:38,200
I feel so fond of that kid.

307
00:16:38,267 --> 00:16:38,833
What?

308
00:16:39,767 --> 00:16:40,600
Hey!

309
00:16:40,667 --> 00:16:41,667
Quit it!

310
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:43,833
Especially you, Emma!

311
00:16:44,400 --> 00:16:46,300
Madam got mad at me
because of you.

312
00:16:46,733 --> 00:16:48,600
I covered you.

313
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:50,500
And I suffered because of it.

314
00:16:50,567 --> 00:16:52,233
She doesn't like me anymore.

315
00:16:52,300 --> 00:16:55,033
Why do you seem
so affected, Mother?

316
00:16:55,100 --> 00:16:58,033
I thought you disliked Olive?

317
00:16:58,100 --> 00:17:03,067
I was supposed to earn
more money from her.

318
00:17:04,233 --> 00:17:06,333
But I lost the opportunity
to earn from her forever.

319
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:07,667
She dislikes me now.

320
00:17:08,567 --> 00:17:10,133
It's okay, Mother.

321
00:17:10,200 --> 00:17:12,433
I don't want her
to mistreat you.

322
00:17:12,500 --> 00:17:14,033
Just find another side hustle.

323
00:17:14,100 --> 00:17:16,000
Hey, she's not mistreating me.

324
00:17:16,633 --> 00:17:18,267
We were about to be
close friends.

325
00:17:20,700 --> 00:17:23,067
If you're friends
with her daughter,

326
00:17:23,133 --> 00:17:25,733
well, I'm friends with her.

327
00:17:27,100 --> 00:17:30,300
They don't have the
same attitude, Mother.

328
00:17:30,367 --> 00:17:32,933
It's easy to make friends
with Mookie.

329
00:17:35,033 --> 00:17:35,767
Why?

330
00:17:36,633 --> 00:17:38,167
Is it not easy with Ma'am Olive?

331
00:17:39,300 --> 00:17:41,000
I won't take care of her
in the hospital

332
00:17:41,067 --> 00:17:42,833
if I don't feel comfortable
with her.

333
00:17:43,667 --> 00:17:47,600
I won't be patient with anyone
I'm not comfortable with.

334
00:17:53,100 --> 00:17:55,067
You see her as a very bad
person.

335
00:17:56,467 --> 00:18:00,667
Even the people at the hospital
gossip about her.

336
00:18:02,400 --> 00:18:03,567
What do they say about her,
Mother?

337
00:18:04,167 --> 00:18:06,733
They said she was not
a real doctor.

338
00:18:07,333 --> 00:18:09,000
They said she was kicked out.

339
00:18:09,067 --> 00:18:10,400
Annoying gossipers.

340
00:18:25,467 --> 00:18:26,067
Emma.

341
00:18:27,333 --> 00:18:28,400
There's tea.

342
00:18:28,467 --> 00:18:30,167
I heard Ma'am Olive
isn't a real doctor.

343
00:18:30,233 --> 00:18:31,067
Is that true?

344
00:18:31,133 --> 00:18:32,533
Mother heard it.

345
00:18:34,500 --> 00:18:35,333
Wait, wait.

346
00:18:36,033 --> 00:18:38,200
You're making me forget.

347
00:18:38,900 --> 00:18:40,200
You did something wrong.

348
00:18:40,267 --> 00:18:42,300
Sorry. Please don't get mad.

349
00:18:42,367 --> 00:18:44,067
I just felt bad for the kid.

350
00:18:44,133 --> 00:18:47,400
I heard she hasn't been
to an arcade.

351
00:18:48,367 --> 00:18:49,367
But you know what?

352
00:18:49,767 --> 00:18:52,100
She was so happy yesterday.

353
00:18:52,867 --> 00:18:54,467
- Let me see.
- Look.

354
00:18:56,133 --> 00:18:57,767
You have a beautiful
photo together.

355
00:18:58,367 --> 00:19:03,200
I just got mad because
you didn't tell me.

356
00:19:03,267 --> 00:19:06,267
And I won't tell Ma'am Olive.

357
00:19:06,333 --> 00:19:08,567
I'm indebted to you.

358
00:19:09,233 --> 00:19:12,467
Because of you, I was able
to attend Aryen's graduation.

359
00:19:13,167 --> 00:19:18,167
And I'm grateful to you
because you brought Mookie out.

360
00:19:19,133 --> 00:19:21,933
This is the first time
I've seen that kid so happy.

361
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:23,667
Her smile is beautiful.

362
00:19:23,733 --> 00:19:25,800
I'm happy for her.

363
00:19:25,867 --> 00:19:26,433
Ma'am.

364
00:19:29,800 --> 00:19:31,267
What are you looking at?

365
00:19:42,200 --> 00:19:44,600
What's with your faces?

366
00:19:44,667 --> 00:19:47,067
I'm asking you what
you're looking at.

367
00:19:48,667 --> 00:19:49,700
Nothing, Ma'am.

368
00:19:51,167 --> 00:19:51,900
Nothing?

369
00:19:54,933 --> 00:19:56,133
No, Ma'am.

370
00:19:57,200 --> 00:19:58,167
Why, Emma?

371
00:19:58,633 --> 00:20:01,600
Is it something that you don't
want me to see?

372
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:07,000
Ma'am, it's just a video
of a drama series

373
00:20:07,067 --> 00:20:08,933
- we watch.
- Yes.

374
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:10,667
It's about a mother and child.

375
00:20:12,067 --> 00:20:12,700
Right?

376
00:20:12,767 --> 00:20:14,133
It's our favorite, Ma'am.

377
00:20:14,200 --> 00:20:15,067
Yes.

378
00:20:15,133 --> 00:20:17,667
I'm not paying you to kill time.

379
00:20:18,367 --> 00:20:20,033
How about you finish your job?

380
00:20:20,833 --> 00:20:21,333
What do you think?

381
00:20:22,233 --> 00:20:22,833
Yes.

382
00:20:23,300 --> 00:20:24,167
We will, Ma'am.

383
00:20:25,567 --> 00:20:26,667
I'm sorry, Ma'am.

384
00:20:45,100 --> 00:20:46,200
How are you feeling?

385
00:20:47,533 --> 00:20:48,267
Mommy.

386
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:53,200
I'm okay.

387
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:01,300
Mommy?

388
00:21:01,367 --> 00:21:02,067
Yes?

389
00:21:03,333 --> 00:21:05,667
I want to ask you something.

390
00:21:06,200 --> 00:21:07,000
What is it?

391
00:21:07,700 --> 00:21:14,400
What will happen to me
if I eat pistachio?

392
00:21:17,900 --> 00:21:19,800
Your body will itch.

393
00:21:20,500 --> 00:21:22,100
You'll get hives.

394
00:21:23,100 --> 00:21:25,300
And your throat will close.

395
00:21:26,300 --> 00:21:27,767
You won't be able to breathe.

396
00:21:28,233 --> 00:21:30,833
And possibly, you'll die.

397
00:21:32,367 --> 00:21:33,733
Even if it's just a little?

398
00:21:34,533 --> 00:21:35,033
Yes.

399
00:21:36,867 --> 00:21:38,300
Why are you asking?

400
00:21:38,367 --> 00:21:40,000
Nothing, Mommy.

401
00:21:40,433 --> 00:21:42,133
I was just curious.

402
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:43,300
Well, don't be.

403
00:21:44,967 --> 00:21:46,033
Stop asking.

404
00:21:50,000 --> 00:21:51,633
Pull your pajamas up.

405
00:21:52,333 --> 00:21:56,733
Mommy, maybe I don't need that
anymore?

406
00:21:56,800 --> 00:22:00,133
You haven't given me an
injection for two days,

407
00:22:00,200 --> 00:22:01,833
and I'm doing okay.

408
00:22:01,900 --> 00:22:02,633
Look at me.

409
00:22:04,967 --> 00:22:10,667
Just because you feel okay
doesn't mean you're doing well.

410
00:22:11,733 --> 00:22:13,367
Fix your pajamas.

411
00:22:13,433 --> 00:22:14,567
Mommy, please.

412
00:22:14,633 --> 00:22:15,500
Just do it!

413
00:22:15,600 --> 00:22:16,533
Mommy.

414
00:22:20,400 --> 00:22:22,300
- Mommy, please.
- Don't give me a hard time.

415
00:22:23,700 --> 00:22:24,467
Mommy!

416
00:22:24,533 --> 00:22:26,900
Mommy, I don't want it!

417
00:22:34,767 --> 00:22:36,467
Will you stop crying?

418
00:22:40,267 --> 00:22:41,100
That's it.

419
00:22:47,067 --> 00:22:47,700
Emma?

420
00:22:47,767 --> 00:22:48,967
Emma!

421
00:22:49,067 --> 00:22:50,600
Emma, wait, where are you going?

422
00:22:50,667 --> 00:22:51,367
What are you doing?
Mookie.

423
00:22:52,100 --> 00:22:54,200
Ma'am Olive is back.

424
00:22:54,267 --> 00:22:55,867
You can't show up to her.

425
00:22:55,933 --> 00:22:57,067
Come on.

426
00:22:57,700 --> 00:23:02,067
Emma, Mookie's real mother
is here already.

427
00:23:03,367 --> 00:23:05,700
You're done being her mother
for a day.

428
00:23:05,767 --> 00:23:08,033
So, stop it. Please.

429
00:23:09,233 --> 00:23:10,733
Ma'am Olive might see you.

430
00:23:10,800 --> 00:23:11,700
Let's go.

431
00:23:11,767 --> 00:23:12,900
Let's go.

432
00:23:12,967 --> 00:23:14,500
Let's just do our job.

433
00:23:24,033 --> 00:23:24,967
Get some rest.

434
00:23:38,667 --> 00:23:39,900
Whose purse is this?

435
00:23:44,167 --> 00:23:45,433
Whose is this?

436
00:23:48,867 --> 00:23:50,000
It's...

437
00:23:51,700 --> 00:23:53,167
It belongs to Flor.

438
00:23:56,167 --> 00:23:57,133
Are you sure?

439
00:23:58,633 --> 00:24:01,267
Did no one else
come into your room?

440
00:24:13,633 --> 00:24:14,433
Who's that?

441
00:24:14,900 --> 00:24:16,300
Is that Emma by the door?

442
00:24:17,967 --> 00:24:19,700
Why don't you call Emma?

443
00:24:19,767 --> 00:24:21,700
She looks after Mookie.

444
00:24:24,667 --> 00:24:28,533
Did Emma take care of you
while I was in the hospital?

445
00:24:29,800 --> 00:24:31,667
Of course not, Mommy.

446
00:24:32,933 --> 00:24:33,933
Tell me the truth.

447
00:24:40,200 --> 00:24:42,933
Whatever Ma'am Olive wants
to do with her child

448
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:44,500
is none of your business.

449
00:24:44,567 --> 00:24:47,167
Madam knows what's best
for her child.

450
00:24:47,233 --> 00:24:52,400
Didn't you say that Ma'am Olive
isn't a certified doctor?

451
00:24:52,467 --> 00:24:55,067
I can't feel my legs again.

452
00:24:55,133 --> 00:24:57,100
I think it's because
of the medicine

453
00:24:57,167 --> 00:24:59,033
my mom injected into me.

454
00:25:01,167 --> 00:25:02,233
Emma?

455
00:25:02,333 --> 00:25:03,000
Mookie?

456
00:25:03,067 --> 00:25:04,267
Because of what you did,

457
00:25:04,333 --> 00:25:06,900
say goodbye to your job
as a laundress.

458
00:25:06,967 --> 00:25:10,400
You're jobless already
because you're fired!

459
00:25:10,467 --> 00:25:11,533
Ma'am.

460
00:25:11,600 --> 00:25:12,533
Get lost!

461
00:25:12,600 --> 00:25:16,067
Mommy, why don't you want me
to be happy?

462
00:25:16,133 --> 00:25:16,600
Happy?
Go ahead!

463
00:25:17,500 --> 00:25:18,100
Eat it!
Do you like this?

464
00:25:19,067 --> 00:25:20,400
Eat it!

465
00:25:20,467 --> 00:25:24,033
You learned to talk back to me
because of that Emma!

466
00:25:24,100 --> 00:25:25,933
- You're ungrateful!
- Mommy!

467
00:25:26,000 --> 00:25:29,533
I know how you feel
because of that Mookie!

468
00:25:29,600 --> 00:25:30,567
Of course, I know!

469
00:25:30,633 --> 00:25:32,400
I lost a child, too!
